SupportAwakenedGenerosity.description: Supports aura skills that affect you and allies, increasing the aura's effect on allies, but preventing it from affecting you at all. Cannot support curse auras, or other auras that only affect enemies. Cannot support skills used by totems. Cannot modify the skills of minions.
SupportAwakenedGenerosity.name: Awakened Generosity

SupportCastOnMeleeKillTriggered.name: Cast on Melee Kill
SupportCastOnMeleeKillTriggered.description: Must support both a melee attack skill and a spell skill to work. The attack skill will trigger a spell when it kills an enemy. Cannot support totems, traps, or mines. Vaal skills, channelling skills, and skills with a reservation cannot be triggered.

SupportGuardiansBlessing.description:
Must support both a skill that creates minions which can be damaged, and
 an aura skill that creates permanent auras around you.
Cannot support triggered skills, banner skills or stance skills.
SupportGuardiansBlessing.name: Guardian's Blessing

SupportSpellTotem.description: Supports spell skills that are not triggered. Instead of casting that spell, you will summon a totem that casts the spell for you.
SupportSpellTotem.name: Spell Totem

SupportStun.name: Stun
SupportStun.description: Supports any skill that hits enemies, making it easier to stun enemies with those skills.

SupportCastWhenDamageTaken.name: Cast when Damage Taken
SupportCastWhenDamageTaken.description: Each supported spell skill will track damage you take, and be triggered when the total damage taken reaches a threshold. Cannot support skills used by totems, traps, or mines. Vaal skills, channelling skills, and skills with a reservation cannot be triggered.

SupportTrauma.name: Trauma
SupportTrauma.description: Supports melee strike skills that do not inherently apply Trauma. Cannot support triggered skills, Vaal skills, or skills used by things other than you. Cannot modify the skills of minions.

SupportAwakenedAddedFireDamage.name: Awakened Added Fire Damage
SupportAwakenedAddedFireDamage.description: Supports any skill that hits enemies.

SupportAncestralCall.description: Supports melee strike skills, causing them to also strike at extra targets simultaneously. The extra targets must be a minimum distance from the user. If supporting a minion attack skill, the minion's skills will not also strike extra targets. Cannot support Vaal skills or triggered skills.
SupportAncestralCall.name: Ancestral Call

SupportMultistrike.description: Supports melee attack skills, making them repeat twice when used, targeting a random enemy each time. Cannot support Vaal skills, channelling skills, travel skills, retaliation skills or triggered skills.
SupportMultistrike.name: Multistrike

SupportOverexertion.description: Supports melee attack skills which can be exerted. Cannot modify the skills of minions. Vaal skills and channelling skills cannot be exerted.
SupportOverexertion.name: Overexertion

SupportArrogance.description: Supports any non-blessing skill with a reservation.
SupportArrogance.name: Arrogance

SupportCorruptingCry.name: Corrupting Cry
SupportCorruptingCry.description: Supports warcry skills. Cannot modify the skills of minions.

SupportAwakenedMultistrike.name: Awakened Multistrike
SupportAwakenedMultistrike.description: Supports melee attack skills, making them repeat three times when used, targeting a random enemy each time. Cannot support Vaal skills, channelling skills, travel skills, retaliation skills or triggered skills.

SupportCruelty.description: Supports any skill that hits enemies. Minions cannot gain Cruelty.

SupportFlamewood.description: Supports skills which summon totems. Cannot modify the skills of minions.
SupportFlamewood.name: Flamewood

AvengingFlame.name: Avenging Flame
AvengingFlame.description: Launches a fiery projectile high into the air, to drop on a target and deal area damage where it lands.

SupportBallistaTotem.name: Ballista Totem
SupportBallistaTotem.description: Supports any bow or wand attack skill, causing it to summon a ballista totem that uses the skill for you.

SupportDamageOnFullLife.description: Supports attack skills, providing a bonus to all damage dealt by those skills while your life is full.
SupportDamageOnFullLife.name: Damage on Full Life

SupportBloodthirst.name: Bloodthirst
SupportBloodthirst.description: Supports attack skills. Cannot support triggered skills, skills which create minions, or skills used by totems, traps or mines.

SupportMoreDuration.name: More Duration
SupportMoreDuration.description: Supports any skill with a duration.

SupportEmpower.name: Empower
SupportEmpower.description: Supports any skill gem. Once this gem reaches level 2 or above, will raise the level of supported gems. Cannot support skills that don't come from gems.

SupportInspiration.name: Inspiration
SupportInspiration.description: Supports any skill. Minions, Totems, Traps and Mines cannot gain Inspiration Charges.

SupportIronGrip.description: Supports attack skills that fire projectiles, making the increase to physical melee damage from strength also increase their physical projectile damage.
SupportIronGrip.name: Iron Grip

SupportBloodlust.description: Supports melee attack skills, causing them to deal more damage against bleeding enemies, but preventing those skills from inflicting bleeding on enemies in any way.
SupportBloodlust.name: Bloodlust

SupportAwakenedBurningDamage.name: Awakened Burning Damage
SupportAwakenedBurningDamage.description: Supports any skill that hits enemies, or can deal burning damage directly.

SupportRuthless.description: Supports melee strike or slam skills. Every third time you use a supported attack, that use of the skill will be more powerful.
SupportRuthless.name: Ruthless

SupportBrutality.description: Supports any skill that deals damage.
SupportBrutality.name: Brutality

SupportEternalBlessing.description: Supports aura skills that reserve life or mana to create auras around you.
SupportEternalBlessing.name: Eternal Blessing

SupportItemQuantity.name: Item Quantity
SupportItemQuantity.description: Supports any skill that can kill enemies.

SupportMaim.description: Supports attack skills, or other skills that can maim enemies.

SupportLessDuration.description: Supports any skill that has a duration.
SupportLessDuration.name: Less Duration

SupportFortify.description: Supports melee attack skills that are not triggered.
SupportFortify.name: Fortify

SupportShockwave.name: Shockwave
SupportShockwave.description: Supports melee attack skills. Cannot support triggered attacks, attacks used by things other than you, or skills which create minions.

SupportFirePenetration.description: Supports any skill that hits enemies, making those hits penetrate enemy fire resistance.
SupportFirePenetration.name: Fire Penetration

SupportIronWill.description: Supports spell skills, making the increase to physical melee damage from strength also increase their spell damage.
SupportIronWill.name: Iron Will

SupportLifeLeech.name: Life Leech
SupportLifeLeech.description: Supports any skill that hits enemies, causing those hits to leech life based on damage dealt.

SupportBluntWeaponShockwave.description: Deals attack damage in an area.

SupportFistofWar.description: Supports slam skills, providing a powerful boost when they're used, with a delay before they can be boosted again. Cannot support Vaal skills or triggered skills. Cannot modify the skills of minions. Only skills you use yourself can receive the boost.
SupportFistofWar.name: Fist of War

SupportLifetap.description: Supports any non-blessing skill. Minions cannot gain the Lifetap buff.

SupportMeleeSplash.description: Supports melee strike skills, causing their melee strike to deal splash damage around each target hit.
SupportMeleeSplash.name: Melee Splash

SupportRage.description: Supports melee attack skills. Minions cannot gain rage.
